FOR YOUR SAFETY - Know how to move out of
this airplane fast.
There is fire-danger any time a landing
is other than normal-particularly when the airplane structure
is damaged. On the back of this card is a floor plan of the
plane you are in.
Familiarize yourself with the location of
the exits.
Note particularly the exits nearest you.
Study
the brace position you should assume during an emergency
landing and also how the doors are opened as shown in the
figures below. When leaving, move immediately to the exits.
Do not go back for coats, purses or other personal items.
YOUR SEAT BELT - It is recommended that seat belts be kept fastened at all times - even when the seat
belt sign is off.
1 Rotate door handle 180 degrees.
Door initially moves inward slight-
ly and then is automatically pow-
ered outward to a fully open posi-
lion.
2 Escape slide automatically drops
and begins inflating when door
is opening.
3 The slide is fully inflated and
ready tor use in a tew seconds.
4 Jump onto the slide in a sitting position using the
closest of the two slide lanes. Do not sit down in the
doorway. Do not try to slow yourself down; special
pads at
the bottom will reduce your speed.
Move
away from the bottom of the slide quickly.
